  "body": "Tim Myers reports getting 403s from the REST API, although they still have data - when rest-api-host-whitelist is disallowing traffic\n\n### Steps to Reproduce (Bug)\n1. start Teku with whitelist that forbids your host\n2. curl -X GET \"http://localhost:5051/node/version\" -H \"accept: text/plain\"\n3. you should get a 403 response with no data\nOR\n4. http://localhost:5051/node/version in browser\n5. you should get a 403 response with no data, like so:\n\n{\n    \"title\": \"Host not authorized\",\n    \"status\": 403,\n    \"type\": \"https://javalin.io/documentation#forbiddenresponse\",\n    \"details\": []\n}\n\n**Expected behavior:** 403 with no content\n\n**Actual behavior:** 403 with content",
